    <text id="B0273T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Fessenden passes along some information about trials of freed blacks during the
                    war. </p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-05-05">May 5th 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Monterey, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Friend Jackson</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I inquired of Mr. Slaven in regard to the trial of freedmen, for horse thievery
                        <orig reg="etc">&amp;c</orig> during the war, and find that
                    <unclear>men</unclear> were tried. There was a man by the name of <del hand="h1"
                    /> (a U.S. scout) tried on some such charge and he has appealed to a "Military
                    Tribunal"</p>

                <p>Remember me to Mrs. Jackson and F.S. Tukey and family.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours truly</salute>
                    <signed>C. B. Fessenden</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">There is not a horse to be hired in this <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                        and I am <hi rend="underline">afraid</hi>, not to be <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> A <del
                            hand="h1"/>
                        <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> to die in this. C.B.F.</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
